channel.title: Portfowarding?
channel.description:
I had it portforwarded before, but then i got my computer wiped. So i went back through and followed the guide on portforward.com. i went to my router site and did the 43594 open step. Its not working tho.. canyouseeme.com says its closed. idk why? i believe i opened it.
Any Idea?

item.title: Portfowarding?
item.dc:creator: @Fridder Fridder
item.description:
@Fridder wrote:

League317:

I have gone back threw and its all setup port is 43594, the adress is my IPv4 adress. I still am not seen? I’m not sure what I have done wrong. Its all correct according to cmd all put in right. It is saving it just does not see me…

Make sure any anti-virus software (McAfee, Norton, AVG, Kaspersky, Comodo, etc) allows port 43594 to go through. Also make sure your server is online first lol.

item.title: Portfowarding?
item.dc:creator: @Fridder Fridder
item.description:
@Fridder wrote:

Open cmd.exe and type in ipconfig, you should see your IPv4 address and your default gateway. Go to your default gateway by typing it into your internet browser’s URL bar. Re-portforward with your changed IPv4 address. By the way, only your IPv4 changed. Your router should save all the settings.
